striction of civil rights, the threat of an arms race in cyberspace, the rivalries between the Great Powers and the increase in right-wing violence. It is precisely in the face of the crisis that international cooperation - and a proactive EU to drive this cooperation forward, both within Europe and globally - is needed to secure peace. Against this background, the Peace Report 2020 analyses current violent conflicts, identifies trends in international foreign, security and development policy and makes recommendations for the Federal Government and the Bundestag. The German peace research institutes (BICC/HSF/IFSH/INEF) have been publishing the report since 1987.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGlobalization. 0aNational security. 0aPeace-building. 4aBewaffnete Konflikte. 4aEntwicklungszusammenarbeit. 4aGewalt. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aInternationale Politik. 4aKonfliktforschung. 4aKrieg. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aSicherheit. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh  aArmed Conflicts.  aConflict Studies.  aDevelopment Aid.  aGlobalization.  aInternational Relations.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aSecurity.  aViolence.  aWar.1 aHSFK Leibniz-Institut Hessische Stiftung Friedens- und Konfliktforschung, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aIFSH Institut für Friedensforschung und Sicherheitspolitik an der Universität Hamburg, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z97831107045